ce:section.ce:para:
In summary, the efficiency of the cell can be altered by varying the WE [55], electrolyte [59], dye [60], and CE [58] material. To the best of our knowledge, the maximum PCE obtained for a particular junction arrangement in DSSC is 14.3%. [60] For WE and CE, there are numerous reports on the use of diverse carbon materials such as graphene, MWCNT, activated carbon, carbon black, graphite and their composites with other metal oxide. Among all of these C-dots are easy and relatively cheaper to synthesis and have special property of band gap tuning. C-dots are also commendable over these carbon materials as a WE in terms of the PCE (
PCE = ( V oc × J sc × FF × 100 ) / P in
), but further improvement is required regarding their use as CE in DSSCs ( Table 2).
